What you need to know:

It was a tough round though for the cool Madoya who overcame a strong challenge from playing mates Abbey Bagalana of Uganda and Muthaiga’s Greg Snow, before posting a final round of two over par 73Before Saturday, his best in any event in the country was a tie with Sigona’s John Wangai in 2018 KCB Golf series, though he won the Entebbe Open in Uganda last yearMeanwhile the Ugandan Bagalana picked up a number of bogeys on both the first and second nine for 78, to drop to fifth place on nine over par 293 while Greg Snow finished fourth on eight over par 292 after firing four over par 75